	        Send us your pictures   ·  Send us your stories It’s been a good day for marijuana users as
the Constitutional Court ruled that the private
use of marijuana is now legal. But while smoking dagga has been
decriminalised there are a few things you should know before lighting up: 1.      
The personal use of dagga is
not a criminal offence, nor is the cultivation or possession of it in private. 2.      
It is illegal to deal
marijuana, sell it to others or smoke it outside of your own home. 3.      
The government still has to
decide how much weed a person may use in private and the age restriction for
use. While the finer points still need to be
ironed out, tweeps have already started sharing their excitement over the ruling:  24.com encourages commentary submitted via MyNews24. Contributions of 200 words or more will be considered for publication.  